          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C fan. Butter the springform tin and line the base. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} with the {{caster-sugar}} for the batter until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} until just smooth. Spread the batter evenly into the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top and bake, 45 to 48 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Peel, core, and halve the {{apple-eating}}s. Cut each half into thin slices, keeping the half intact. Fan each half out and lay it on the batter surface in a ring, pressing each lightly into the batter. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "sunken fruit technique",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yefzz000098v4whnihejo"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": the batter will rise around the apples as it bakes. Mix the {{caster-sugar}} for the topping with the {{cinnamon-ground}} and scatter over the apples. Bake for 45 to 48 minutes until the batter is set around the apples and a skewer inserted into the batter (not an apple) comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes before releasing the springform. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
